race.comment: PAW LOU LOU (1) has been in the minors the last two, the latest showing strong pace early but gathered in and finished a 3.5 lengths second over 515m Sandown in 29.66. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Winning claims. FLEETWOOD EROS (2) finished well back at this track last time when a 11 length eighth (28.40) but recorded second best time of the card when winning five back. One of the better hopes. PAW HARRIS (6) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (30.01) last time in a Grade 5 at Sandown. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from four starts. Should be about the mark. QUEEN KIMETTO (7) placed from this box last start - cannot be ignored.
